- Post Title: skeleton to smd extractor (wip)

This thread is a reminder for myself to get the skel2smd extractor released 'til the end of 2017.
(I'm struggeling with this idea since 18 + 9 months now and seems I've to push myself a little bit.)

It shares the same basic idea like hex2obj, that ugly mesh extractor, that requires to search for "random" parameters as  those guys tend to slander who don't get familiar with it.  

But currently that's the quickest approach I could think of instead of fully researching formats again and again.

The skel2smd extractor got an hkx button now. It's for skeletons only and requires 3 addresses and the bonecount to be found/entered manually. Most people aren't fond of this and so I'm thinking (ages now) of a way how to get those params automatically without completely analysing the whole beast (Dark Souls 3 skeleton):
[](http://www.pic-upload.de/view-30720685/hkx_skeleton.jpg.html)
(ok, the bonecount (00 00 00 5B) is located before the table of parenting IDs)

smd data: [viewtopic.php?f=16&t=12857&p=118757&hil ... al#p118757](http://forum.xentax.com/viewtopic.php?f=16&t=12857&p=118757&hilit=+additional#p118757)

Here's another skeleton, Aria.smd from killer instinct Aria.kihkx (copy code to file and name it Aria.smd):
